cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.DB

The paper presents a deep learning method for detecting patients with a rare disease using longitudinal medical claims data. This involves sequence modeling using recurrent neural networks and generative adversarial networks to boost rare disease class. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a deep learning model. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing of medical claims data. Additionally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible sub-categories as the paper involves the use of large longitudinal medical claims data to improve patient outcomes.
